  2018,"10",/general-conference/2018/10/all-must-take-upon-them-the-name-given-of-the-father,Elder Paul B. Pieper,43,"“When we witness ourwillingnessto take upon us the name of Jesus Christ, we are signifying our commitment to do all that we can to achieve eternal life in the kingdom of our Father. We are expressing our candidacy—our determination to strive for—exaltation in the celestial kingdom. …"
  2018,"10",/general-conference/2018/10/all-must-take-upon-them-the-name-given-of-the-father,Elder Paul B. Pieper,44,"“… What we witness is not that wetakeupon us his name but that we arewillingto do so. In this sense, our witness relates to some future event or status whose attainment is not self-assumed, but depends on the authority or initiative of the Savior himself” (Dallin H. Oaks, “Taking upon Us the Name of Jesus Christ,” 82, 83)."
